    "narrative": "Today\u2019s offensive outlook is anchored by **Mickey Moniak** (75.98) and **James Wood** (71.11), who represent our highest-upside plays. **Mickey Moniak** benefits from a massive park factor boost (+14%) and a favorable matchup against Mike Burrows, while **James Wood** leverages his prime leadoff spot (+10% order bonus) and a soft matchup against the lefty Matthew Liberatore. Meanwhile, **Vinnie Pasquantino** (68.03) and **Jazz Chisholm Jr.** (67.99) are locked into strong positions, with **Vinnie Pasquantino** capitalizing on a significant dynamic platoon edge (+14%) against the right-handed arms of the opposition. These four players provide the ceiling we need to offset the scarcity in our SB targets, as we are prioritizing the high-efficiency environment created by favorable SP skill gaps.\n\nThe most difficult bench decision involved **Brice Turang** (47.83), who remains our premier speed threat but fell just short of the starting cut due to a daunting matchup against Garrett Crochet. While **Brice Turang** holds an elite leadoff projection, the negative impact of facing an ace (-19% SP skill) and the prevailing winds suppressed his efficiency score relative to the rest of the utility mix. We are also monitoring the \"Lineup Pending\" status for **Dalton Rushing**, **Jose Caballero**, **Austin Riley**, **Giancarlo Stanton**, and **Josh Naylor**. While we have baked in historical batting positions, any shift down the order for these hitters\u2014specifically **Giancarlo Stanton** or **Jose Caballero**\u2014could necessitate a move to the bench to protect our daily game caps.\n\nBeyond the pending lineups, we must navigate a persistent wind-in risk affecting several core starters, including **Gabriel Moreno**, **Jose Caballero**, **Corbin Carroll**, **Tyler Soderstrom**, and **Giancarlo Stanton**, which has shaved roughly 9% off their baseline potential. Despite the wind, **Corbin Carroll** remains a critical start at 60.37; his 92% steal probability against a slow-delivery pitcher makes him a unique asset that transcends his adjusted efficiency score. Keep a close eye on the pre-game weather reports, as any increase in those wind gusts could force us to pivot toward the safer floors of our bench, such as **Zach McKinstry**, should the lineups for our utility spots shift unfavorably.",
